  "name": "Volatility Contraction Breakout Strategy",
  "description": "This strategy focuses on identifying periods of low volatility using Bollinger Bands. It triggers a watch state when the Bollinger Bands Width reaches its lowest point over the last 60 periods, and enters a long position if the next candle closes above the upper band after the watch state.",
  "algorithm_type": "TechnicalPattern",
  "prompt": "I want to build a strategy that trades based on volatility contraction breakouts. Specifically, calculate the 14-period Bollinger Bands Width. When the Bollinger Bands Width reaches its lowest value over the past 60 periods (indicating volatility compression), set a \"watch\" state. Enter a long position if, after this watch state is triggered, the next candle\u2019s close breaks above the upper Bollinger Band, on higher volume than the previous 5-period average. Enter a short position if the close breaks below the lower Bollinger Band with above-average volume. Exit any position when price closes back inside the Bollinger Bands or hits a 3% stop-loss from entry. This approach looks for explosive moves after range contraction, filtered by volume.",
